Enraged parents of 10  pupils who were  allegedly subjected to corporal punishment  by teachers at Osborn Senior Secondary School in KwaBhaca (formerly Mount Frere), Eastern Cape, want action taken against the teachers. A group of pupils living in the school's hostel were allegedly given lashings for making a noise  on Monday. One of the parents told Sowetan she was shocked when she received a WhatsApp voice note from her crying daughter. The mother asked not to be identified for the safety of her children. For theÂ  full article please visit SowetanLIVE.